Title:
Tutorial example  - IR photo-electron spectrum of hydrogen

The purpose of this exercise is to explore the calculation of IR spectra
    in linear polarization, learn to assess accuracy and convergence

# TIMING ~1+1 min for tRecX + spectral analysis with given parameters
(results with Intel i7 on laptop)

[TASK] perform convergence studies
the initial parameters in this file are adjusted to yield ~ 10% accuracy in much of the spectrum
Verify by varying
  Eta-axis  (i.e. angular momenta)
  Rn-axis   radial basis
  
[TASK] note the relation between the Rn-size and Eta-size
the simulation volume growth is 2-dimensional!

#define NEL  8
#define ORD 12
#define SIZ 5

#define BOX NEL*SIZ

Spectrum: radialPoints=200, plot=total, iSurff=true

# basis sizes eta,r=30,40 appear to be good for 10% accuracy in relevant range
Axis: name,order,lower end, upper end,functions,nElem
 Phi,1
 Eta,30,-1,1, assocLegendre{Phi}
 Rn,ORD, 0.,BOX,RpowL*polynomial,NEL
 Rn,30, BOX,Infty,polExp[0.5]

Absorption: kind, axis, theta, upper
ECS,Rn,0.3,BOX

# Note: full long-range Coulomb - spectrum will change with box-size
Operator: hamiltonian='1/2<<Laplacian>>-<1><1><1/Q>'
Operator: interaction='iLaserA0[t]<<D/DZ>>'
Operator: expectationValue='<1><1><chi[0,20]>'

# writes population of field-free states 0,1,2,3,4 to output and expec files
Occupation: states=0:5

Laser: shape, I(W/cm2), FWHM, lambda(nm)
cos8, 2.e14, 3. OptCyc, 800.

# operatorThreshold -- disregard operations that contribute below this value (default is 0)
# observe impact on compute time and accuracy
# no TimePropagation:end specified - propagation ends at end of pulse (needs iSurff for correct spectra)
TimePropagation: print,cutEnergy,accuracy,operatorThreshold,fixStep
 0.25 OptCyc,30,5e-7,5e-7,0.08

